  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 3
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The two that left?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Left owed nothing, owing nothing. Struck clean. The lowlands pay coin in winter; I could not argue the sum, so I did not argue it.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Why keep me?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The paddies take six hands at the least. Five sleep here now. You are the sixth. If a better sixth comes by, the book will say so.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Just the meals?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Six hands' work, five men fed. The sixth eats. That is the whole of it.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Just the meals?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Six hands' work, five men fed. The sixth eats. That is the whole of it.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"And if there were?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Then the house's claim comes first, while you eat its rice. After that — whoever can find you. So far nobody has asked.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The gate and gateyard are yours to work now — stores come and go here, and Yohei sets up his stall on market days.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The terraced home paddies open to you — the rice that feeds the house.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "They give you the lean space between the woodpiles: a mat, a chipped bowl, a nail for the coat. It is not much, and it is not anyone else's.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You begin to mark the turning of the days, and the four seasons with them.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Rank ↑ — The day-hand 日雇",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The estate's own state of repair is yours to tend now — spend the house's surplus to shore it up.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The rice you clear and grow is food, not only trade — a plain bowl of it fills a hollow belly and puts you back to work the faster.",
   "count": 1
  }
